    "stix_id": "indicator--efc95c8903a3532e8c83a3d318e6e64d",
    "title": "ODINI Malware Uses CPU Magnetic Emissions to Breach Faraday-Shielded Air-Gapped Computers",
    "description": "ODINI is a sophisticated proof-of-concept malware capable of extracting sensitive information from air-gapped computers protected by Faraday cages. By modulating the targeted computer&#8217;s CPU workload to generate low-frequency magnetic fields, this covert channel successfully transmits data through advanced physical isolation barriers. Developed by a team led by Mordechai Guri at Israel&#8217;s Ben-Gurion University, the ODINI [&#8230;] \n The post  ODINI Malware Uses CPU Magnetic Emissions t",
